        <headline>Beach Hazards Statement issued July 30 at 3:48PM EDT until August 1 at 12:00AM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...High swim risk from high wave action and strong
currents. Dangerous swimming conditions are expected.

* WHERE...Huron, Sanilac and St. Clair Counties.

* WHEN...From Thursday morning through Thursday evening.

* IMPACTS...Strong currents can pull swimmers into deep water
and prevent return to shore.
</description>
        <instruction>Remain out of the water to avoid hazardous swimming conditions.</instruction>
